related_questions.question: What is the coldest month in Los Angeles?
related_questions.snippet: Temperatures in Los Angeles rarely get too hot or too cold with July and January being the warmest and coldest months respectively.
related_questions.title: January

related_questions.question: How hot will LA be in the summer?
related_questions.snippet: Average high temperatures are in the lower 80's F (26-28 C) with overnight lows in the lower 60's F (15-17 C). During this season, there is essentially no rainfall, and both July and August average less than 0.05 of an inch (1.27 mm) of monthly precipitation.
related_questions.title: Climate of Los Angeles - Wikipedia

related_questions.question: Is LA humid or dry?
related_questions.snippet: However, compared to other parts of the United States, the humidity levels in Los Angeles are generally lower. The city is known for its Mediterranean climate, which brings dry, warm summers and mild, wet winters. Does Los Angeles get humid in summer? Yes, but usually only a few days out of the summer.
